  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equation.}\n\\begin{equation}\nH\n=\n\\frac{p^2}{2m}\n+\n\\frac{1}{2}m\\omega^2 q^2\n+\n\\delta H .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Ladder Constraint.}\n\\begin{equation}\n[a,a^\\dagger]=1 .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nThe ordinary quantum harmonic oscillator has Hamiltonian:\n\n\\begin{equation}\nH_0\n=\n\\frac{p^2}{2m}\n+\n\\frac{1}{2}m\\omega^2 q^2 .\n\\end{equation}\n\nNear the TZP, curvature-sensitive or zero-point corrections are collected into a perturbative term $\\delta H$:\n\n\\begin{equation}\nH = H_0+\\delta H .\n\\end{equation}\n\nSubstituting $H_0$ gives:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\boxed{\nH\n=\n\\frac{p^2}{2m}\n+\n\\frac{1}{2}m\\omega^2 q^2\n+\n\\delta H .\n}\n\\end{equation}\n\nThe ladder algebra remains admissible if the correction preserves the oscillator structure:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n[a,a^\\dagger]=1 .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\nThe TZP-modified oscillator keeps the standard oscillator core while adding a curvature-sensitive correction.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
